WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.140 --> 00:00:08.010
- Generally, we see that
as chats get longer,

2
00:00:08.010 --> 00:00:09.480
just the amount of context

3
00:00:09.480 --> 00:00:12.270
Gemini has to keep track of gets bigger.

4
00:00:12.270 --> 00:00:16.740
And so you may see some of the
quality start to deteriorate,

5
00:00:16.740 --> 00:00:19.143
you know, many, many, many turns later.

6
00:00:20.370 --> 00:00:21.360
That could be a good time

7
00:00:21.360 --> 00:00:24.453
for you to kind of restart the chat.

8
00:00:24.670 --> 00:00:28.470
The way... You know, one way you could do that

9
00:00:28.470 --> 00:00:30.210
is actually just ask Gemini,

10
00:00:30.210 --> 00:00:32.100
like, "Can you summarize this thread?

11
00:00:32.100 --> 00:00:33.810
I'm gonna start another thread,"

12
00:00:33.810 --> 00:00:36.000
and get an output

13
00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:37.560
of, like, what has
happened in this thread,

14
00:00:37.560 --> 00:00:38.820
what you have tried.

15
00:00:38.820 --> 00:00:39.930
I would still upload,

16
00:00:39.930 --> 00:00:41.580
if you, you know, had any attachments

17
00:00:41.580 --> 00:00:42.570
in that original thread,

18
00:00:42.570 --> 00:00:44.073
I would re-upload them again.

19
00:00:44.940 --> 00:00:47.977
But you can do that same format of, like,

20
00:00:47.977 --> 00:00:50.430
"I was working on this problem.

21
00:00:50.430 --> 00:00:54.300
Here are the relevant docs attached again.

22
00:00:54.300 --> 00:00:55.890
I have already done this much,"

23
00:00:55.890 --> 00:00:58.020
like, paste in that summarized content,

24
00:00:58.020 --> 00:01:00.436
and then ask your next
query of what to do.